+{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01ENMoCuF3sFFLZWEA5q3CcL","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now I understand. The test at line 326 adds a `2024-02-01` invoice. The test expects Jan=3 (10th, 25th, 31st) and Feb=2 (15th, 1st). But it gets Jan=4, meaning the Feb 1st invoice is being counted as January.\n\nThe issue is: `process.env.TZ = 'America/New_York'` is set. When `new Date('2024-02-01T00:00:00Z')` is created, `getMonth()` (non-UTC) would give January in EST because UTC midnight is 7pm the previous day in EST. BUT the code uses `getUTCMonth()` on line 28... wait, no it uses `getMonth()`.\n\nLet me re-read reporting.ts line 28 carefully:\n\n```js\nconst d = new Date(inv.date + 'T00:00:00Z');\nconst month = d.getMonth() + 1; // 1-indexed\n```\n\nThere it is! The code creates a UTC date but then uses `getMonth()` (local time) instead of `getUTCMonth()`. Since TZ is `America/New_York`, UTC midnight on Feb 1 = Jan 31 at 7pm EST, so `getMonth()` returns 0 (January) instead of 1 (February).\n\nNow I have all 3 bugs clearly identified. Let me fix them."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":859,"cache_read_input_tokens":30037,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":859},"output_tokens":3,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"cb37e3a9-ecc1-423e-ad63-8ba181e5ba8e","uuid":"69b366cd-58c6-4039-bd10-830371b0e1b9"}
